description.displayText: Ana cared for my 17 month old son and was great with him. She was punctual and dependable and had glowing reviews. And because I was traveling on business with my son to multiple NYC locations she was gracious enough to come to where we were. She even watched him New Year's Eve! I mean she even brought a toy for my son to play with knowing he was in a hotel and far from home. It was a sweet gesture. Hire her!

description.displayText: Ana responded immediately to my request for a babysitter and called me to speak before the first day. She arrived right on time and was super friendly with my family and confident with my 3 month old. Ana sent pictures and kept records of feeding amounts and times and when my son slept and had diaper changes which I appreciated. She definitely had a natural way with babies! Highly recommend!

description.displayText: Ana has been our full time Nanny for the past year and we absolutely LOVE her! She has been caring for our son since the age of 3 months. He is now moving on to daycare, but any family would be lucky to have Ana!! She is very good with our son, he gets very excited to see her and he has really thrived in her care.

description.displayText: Had a great experience with Ana when she took care of our daughter on a Saturday evening. Seemed very in tune with my toddler and very conscientious. Will definitely hire again.

description.displayText: Ana came in for me while my regular babysitter was in LA for the week. An was our first non-family member to watch our daughter for an extended time. I was worried that my daughter would not take to her but she automatically did. She was extremely flexible with my mother in law who wanted to watch her a couple hours in the middle of the day. She was also very patient and happy with our (then 7mo old) daughter. She kept a very detailed schedule and our daughter really enjoyed her company. I would recommend her to anyone looking to hire a short term/long term nanny.

description.displayText: Greetings:  You will be very happy and pleased with Ana. She is absolutely amazing  - full of energy, lots of fun, well disciplined, healthy habits and routines, listens and understands, and builds great character and morals with children.   Here is our perspective and experience: She is reliable - always good about schedules for duty, play dates, neighborhood -park playground - museum - library visits, feeding (pumped breast milk or formula), healthy meals, no junk food or candy, sleep, clothes, learning and social development, and flexible on notice.  She takes time to read, play, and listen to our children. She played nice quiet classical music and worked on their skills with games, toys, art, and books.  She found nearby play groups for making friends. Our kids always had a great time with her as babies, toddlers and kindergarteners.  She would work with our kids and come up with terrific stories, have a fun time and behave well.  Even though they are in elementary school now - they still look forward to her phone calls and visits.  She is an incredible Nanny and terrific care provider - we can always call, text or email her at a moment's notice and she will get back to us as schedules allow within a timely manner.  Sometimes it is tricky as parents to let go or listen to others, we were confident and are so grateful we had Ana.   Our kids completely adore her.  Ana is incredibly trustworthy - she will write down and tell you everything that happens during the day and gives great advise.  It is very comfortable to talk with her and get great feedback.   We were very happy with her and highly recommend her for Nanny services.  Her strengths: listening, artistic, gentle-disciplined care, clean, non-smoker, walks in the neighborhood or playground park, smart, reliable, awareness of needs, cheery and fun to be with, safe, organized, focused and forward thinking.  Her weaknesses: hmm, none really.   Have a nice week.  All the best,  Mimi & Dan
